Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
Hi, now let us learn how to cross the street together. First of all, let us stand here. Now, we look at left side and see there is no car driving through. Then, we look at the right side. There is no car coming either. Then, we look at the left side again. It is all clear that there is not car. Now, let us cross the street.